^*BThe Bridge Magicians^*N is a large collection of hands that were played brilliantly by various Polish experts. Poland has asserted itself as one of the strongest bridge nations in the world during the past 10 years and ^*BThe Bridge Magicians^*N displays plenty of evidence for why this has happened. This book features hands that were played by 25 Polish experts. Interesting biographical material is also included. Many of these players are well known throughout the world, but some of them are not famous outside of Poland (which further illustrates the depth of bridge talent in this country). We highly recommend this book for all players of at least intermediate level.

This week's deal was played by ^*BCezary Balicki^*N in a pairs event is Slawa last year. Cezary is considered by many (including us) to be one of the very best players in the world today. As you will see from this week's deal, the term "bridge magician" is quite appropriate for describing a player with Cezary's ability. Cezary's technical skills are second to none, but his tremendous card reading and table presence also contribute to his tendency to win a lot of tricks as declarer.|
